WEBVTT

00:00.338 --> 00:05.045
We use "under" to talk about a position that is below something.

00:05.669 --> 00:06.495
For example:

00:06.702 --> 00:08.701
The dogs are under the table.

00:10.192 --> 00:12.120
We sat under the tree.

00:13.075 --> 00:15.053
The cat is under the bed.

00:19.261 --> 00:24.395
We use "above" when we locate someone or something in a higher position.

00:25.111 --> 00:25.816
For example:

00:26.305 --> 00:27.921
The stars are above you.

00:28.763 --> 00:30.857
He put his hands above his head.

00:32.045 --> 00:34.673
The plane flies above the clouds.

